WEBVTT

00:00:00.370 --> 00:00:01.530
<v Instructor>Now, Amazon Comprehend</v>

00:00:01.530 --> 00:00:03.820
is a very simple service from an exam perspective.

00:00:03.820 --> 00:00:05.610
All you need to know is that Comprehend is

00:00:05.610 --> 00:00:06.540
to comprehend stuff,

00:00:06.540 --> 00:00:09.928
so it is for Natural Language Processing, or NLP.

00:00:09.928 --> 00:00:11.870
So anytime you will see NLP on the exam,

00:00:11.870 --> 00:00:14.020
you would think Amazon Comprehend.

00:00:14.020 --> 00:00:17.830
Now what it is, it is a fully managed and serverless service

00:00:17.830 --> 00:00:20.040
and it will use machine learning to find insights

00:00:20.040 --> 00:00:22.840
and relationships in your text.

00:00:22.840 --> 00:00:24.758
For example, it can understand what is the language

00:00:24.758 --> 00:00:27.490
of the text, it can extract key phrases,

00:00:27.490 --> 00:00:30.460
places, people, brands, or events from that text.

00:00:30.460 --> 00:00:33.340
It can understand, do a sentiment analysis to understand

00:00:33.340 --> 00:00:37.570
how positive or negative the text you're analyzing is.

00:00:37.570 --> 00:00:40.320
It can also analyze a text using tokenization

00:00:40.320 --> 00:00:41.290
and parts of speech.

00:00:41.290 --> 00:00:42.900
It also has audio.

00:00:42.900 --> 00:00:45.190
And finally, it can organize a collection

00:00:45.190 --> 00:00:48.720
of text files by topic, and find topics itself.

00:00:48.720 --> 00:00:51.850
So, Comprehend is really about getting a lot of data in

00:00:51.850 --> 00:00:53.010
and then Comprehend will do the rest

00:00:53.010 --> 00:00:55.660
to try to understand the meaning of that data.

00:00:55.660 --> 00:00:58.067
So it's about taking text or unstructured data

00:00:58.067 --> 00:01:00.900
and structuring it around these features.

00:01:00.900 --> 00:01:03.500
So some sample use cases of Natural Language Processing,

00:01:03.500 --> 00:01:06.770
or NLP, are for example, to analyze customer interaction.

00:01:06.770 --> 00:01:09.640
So say you have a bunch of customers sending you emails

00:01:09.640 --> 00:01:11.800
and you want to understand overall based

00:01:11.800 --> 00:01:14.190
on your support service what leads to a positive

00:01:14.190 --> 00:01:16.260
or negative experience from your customers.

00:01:16.260 --> 00:01:18.840
So we use Comprehend to extract these features

00:01:18.840 --> 00:01:20.630
and then you will have the business insight

00:01:20.630 --> 00:01:21.694
and then you can improve your business,

00:01:21.694 --> 00:01:24.050
thanks to that analysis.

00:01:24.050 --> 00:01:26.020
You can also, for example, create

00:01:26.020 --> 00:01:29.080
and group articles by topics that Comprehend will uncover.

00:01:29.080 --> 00:01:30.520
So imagine you have a lot of articles

00:01:30.520 --> 00:01:32.450
and you want to group them together instead

00:01:32.450 --> 00:01:34.740
of going to them one by one, you would feed them

00:01:34.740 --> 00:01:36.920
into Comprehend and then it would output you

00:01:36.920 --> 00:01:38.810
the topics you need to group them by.

00:01:38.810 --> 00:01:39.643
So that's it.

00:01:39.643 --> 00:01:41.500
So again, a bit more information than what you need,

00:01:41.500 --> 00:01:44.060
but Comprehend from an exam perspective is

00:01:44.060 --> 00:01:45.760
for Natural Language Processing.

00:01:45.760 --> 00:01:46.593
So hope you liked it,

00:01:46.593 --> 00:01:48.520
and I will see you in the next lecture.